author: news.com.au
title: Australian market set to open higher
text:
Wednesday posted a third straight gain.
 higher after a rise in commodities prices set international bourses rallying.
At 0645 AEDT on Thursday, the December 31 points at 5,221.
Locally, in economic news on Thursday, Reserve Bank of Australia head of economic research John Simon is slated to speak at the Paul Woolley Centre for the study of Capital Market Dysfunctionality Conference in Sydney. The Australian Nickel Conference is on in Perth.
In equities news, the Bank of Queensland is expected to post full year results, while Ansell has its annual general meeting in Melbourne.
 Wednesday recovered from a midday slump to post a third straight gain, driven by a sustained rally among energy companies.
 was up 30.5 points, or 0.59 per cent, at 5,197.9 was up 29.4 points, or 0.57 per cent, at 5,228.4
